## Vercel Speed Insights Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js project.

### Changes Made

#### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package (version determined by npm)
- Package added to project dependencies in `package.json`
- Lock file (`package-lock.json`) updated with new dependency

#### 2. Configuration
Modified `app/layout.tsx`:
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the root layout, placed next to the existing `<Analytics />` component in the body

### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), the implementation:
- Uses the Next.js App Router specific import path (`@vercel/speed-insights/next`)
- Places the component in the root layout file for app-wide tracking
- Follows the existing pattern already established with Vercel Analytics

### Files Modified
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights import and component
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency tree

### Verification
- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ TypeScript compilation passed
- ✅ No new linting errors introduced
- ✅ Component properly integrated alongside existing Analytics

### Next Steps
To activate Speed Insights:
1. Enable Speed Insights in your Vercel dashboard
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. Performance metrics will appear in the dashboard after users visit your site

The Speed Insights feature will automatically add routes scoped at `/_vercel/speed-insights/*` after deployment.
